  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency WASH Response Women, Men, Girls and Boys in Conflict Affected LGAs, Borno State, Nigeria.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed emergency response project will address critical gaps and protection concerns within WASH sector to meet the needs of vulnerable women, men, girl and boys living in 1 out of the 11 priority conflict-affected LGAs of Borno State: Gwoza. This intervention aims to increase access to lifesaving WaSH services for IDPs and host communities with the highest needs within one of the most underfunded sectors.

Reduction of health risks and increased dignity of affected women, men, girls and boys through provision of adequate and safe drinking water via water trucking (at least 4,666 beneficiaries) in Pulka, rehabilitation and upgrading of WaSH facilities destroyed by windstorms and floods (4,000 beneficiaries), distribution and replenishment of hygiene kits to support safe and appropriate household hygiene with focus on cholera prevention (minimum 5,000 individuals), reinforcement of community capacity on OampM of WaSH facilities for their sustainability.</narrative>
  </description>
